    {% call components.section("Style") -%}
    <p>There are two link variants available for use.</p>
          <table style="width:100%;">
          <tbody><tr>
            <th>Variant Name</th>
            <th>Usage</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Inline link</td>
            <td>The Inline link variant can be used inside of a line of text or paragraph to entice a user to take a less important&nbsp;action.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Call to action link</td>
            <td>The Call to action link variant can be used on its own or near content to entice a user to take a more important&nbsp;action.</td>
         </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <br>
        <h4>Visual elements</h4>
        <p>Each link variant has different styles depending on how they are used with content.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Inline</b> link - Text with or without a color or underline.</li>
            <li><b>External link</b> - Text with an external link icon to the right.</li>
            <li><b>Primary or Secondary call to action link</b> - Bolded text placed inside of a background or border container.</li>
            <li><b>Default call to action link</b> - Bolded text that includes an arrow or icon to the right.</li>
        </ul>
