    {% call components.section("Usage") -%}

        <h3>When to use</h3>

        <p>Links should be used when a user needs to jump to content on the same page, visit a page within the same domain, or visit a page within another domain.</p>

        <!-- Add image of component in layout or somewhere else -->

        {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
        <img src="{{ '/assets/link/usage-block.svg' | url }}" alt="Example of how links should be used within a domain or to an external domain" style="--inline-img-max-width: 754px;">
        {%- endcall %}

        <h4> Content</h4>
        <p>Links are navigational elements, so the text needs to accurately communicate the destination. Inconsistent experiences might lead to distrust, lessening the satisfaction of a user during their journey. When writing link content, Inline links should be more descriptive to help a user better understand the destination whereas Call to action links should be more action-oriented to entice a user to make a selection.</p>
         <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
         <img src="{{ '/assets/link/content-warning-alert.svg' | url }}" alt="Warning alert: Link text needs to be written clearly in order to be underestood,so use no more than four or five words." style="--inline-img-max-width: 1000px;">

        </div>
      
        <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
         <img src="{{ '/assets/link/descriptive-vs-action-oriented.svg' | url }}" alt="" style="--inline-img-max-width: 1000px;">
        </div>
        <h4>Images</h4>
        <p>Photos or images can be links as long as there is supporting content nearby explaining that a selection can be made, like a headline or Call to action link variant. Do not hide links in photos or images otherwise a user will miss the opportunity to make a selection if they cannot see the link.</p>
        <h4>Buttons</h4>
        <p>Do not use a link if an action should be triggered instead, like submitting a form, changing a state, or manipulating data.</p>
        <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4" >
         <img src="{{ '/assets/link/form.svg' | url }}" alt="Example of when not to use a link if ation should be triggered insteadsuc has submitting a form, changing a state, or manipulating data " style="--inline-img-max-width: 1000px;">
        
        
    {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.section("Behavior") -%}
    <h3>Internal pages</h3>
    <p>If a user selects a link within redhat.com, they should be directed to content within the redhat.com domain. In this situation, a new tab or window is <b>not opened.</b></p>
    <h3>External pages</h3>
    <p>A user will be directed to another domain if they select the Inline link variant with an <b>external</b> link icon. For example, if a user needs to be directed to another website with different content or to complete a separate task, a new tab or window (depending on their browser configuration) is opened so they may complete that task and then return to the original task.</p>
        <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
